Steps to deploy the next.js:-

Setup of Local :-
1. Edit your schema.prisma file:
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

2. Option A: Use Supabase (easy, free, cloud-based)
Sign up at supabase.com.
Create a new project.
Go to Project Settings → Database → Connection string.
Copy the postgresql://... connection string.

3. Update Your Local .env
Open .env and set:
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://<username>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<database>

4. .dockerignore
Remove any line that says package-lock.json

5.  Check lockfile version
"lockfileVersion": 2

6. Add a postinstall Script in package.json
"scripts": {
  // ...existing scripts...
  "postinstall": "prisma generate"
}

Step 4: Install Dependencies
In your project folder, run:
npm install


Step 5: Generate Prisma Client
npx prisma generate


Step 6: Run Migrations to Set Up the Database
npx prisma migrate dev --name init


Deployment:
1. Set below build command:
npm install && npx prisma migrate deploy && npx prisma generate && npm run build
